    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (74.41) serving as our anchor; he provides the highest floor and ceiling against Slade Cecconi, benefiting significantly from his elite xwOBA and a favorable matchup that boosts his base projection. **Trea Turner** (70.46) remains a critical cornerstone, and while his aggressive base-stealing potential is mitigated slightly by a strong opposing catcher, his leadoff spot against Colin Rea makes him a primary source for both runs and SBs. **Kyle Schwarber** (69.69) rounds out our elite tier, as his high-contact metrics against Rea suggest he is primed to capitalize on the park factors. While **Hyeseong Kim** (60.67) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (60.49) sit right on the \"Strong\" start threshold, both are must-starts today; **Hyeseong Kim** thrives against the high-xERA mark of Jose Quintana, and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** gains enough of a platoon boost to offset the risk posed by Aaron Nola\u2019s strikeout stuff.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved our utility slot, where **Junior Caminero** (55.86) was preferred over **Dillon Dingler** (36.10). While **Junior Caminero** faces a challenge in Rhett Lowder, his higher base projection and batting order security ultimately eclipsed **Dillon Dingler**, who fell well below the 40-point floor due to a poor platoon setup against Sonny Gray. We are monitoring the status of **Victor Scott II** (43.78) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (43.41) closely; both are marginal plays, but we are keeping them active to hunt for stolen bases and counting stats. We remain sidelined with **Christian Yelich** on the IL, while **Carson Benge** and **Gary Sanchez** are unavailable due to scheduling. All lineup slots remain subject to change pending official confirmation, but we are proceeding with this configuration to maximize our efficiency in a competitive Roto environment.",
